  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2023-07-27",
    "date": "2024-05-22T14:15:38Z",
    "text": "This bill directs the Agricultural Marketing Service to establish a grant program for commercial specialty crop producers to acquire equipment and provide related training.\n\nFunds must be used for mechanized or automated systems and tools that increase the efficiency of a task or reduce human labor for a specific activity (e.g., low-dust harvesting tools and equipment, sorting machines, and crop monitoring and analytics equipment and tools).\n\nThe bill includes a minimum 50% cost-sharing requirement."
  },
